t.uk/resources/683296/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683296/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-02-02","Alcoholic Drinks: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what tax liabilities would result from a 3.2 per cent increase in duty on UK wine and spirits for (a) UK consumers and (b) businesses.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","62915"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683297","HM Treasury","false","2017-02-09","<p>In accordance with the Treasury’s policy we do not provide personal data on individual employees.</p><p> </p><p>The Treasury promotes equality of opportunity in employment to ensure that its workforce is representative of the community it serves and that the Department attracts and retains talented employees.</p><p> </p><p>Information on the diversity of the Treasury’s employees is published in the Treasury’s Annual Report and Accounts which are available at: https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-annual-report.</p><p> </p>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby",,"2017-02-09T14:41:08.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683297/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683297/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683297/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-02-02","Treasury: Senior Civil Servants","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the (a) ethnicity, (b) gender, (c) disability status, (d) educational background and (e) socio-economic status is of the three most senior officials of his Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","62897"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683298","HM Treasury","false","2017-02-07","<p>The Chancellor meets regularly with Cabinet colleagues for discussions on a wide range of issues.</p><p> </p><p>Gambling regulation is a matter for the Department for Culture, Media and Sport (DCMS) and the Gambling Commission. DCMS will publish an impact assessment on any changes proposed as a result of the Triennial Review.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2017-02-07T15:16:56.63Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683298/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683298/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683298/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-02-02","Gaming Machines","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport on the potential effect on tax receipts of proposals that are being considered under the Triennial Review of gaming machine stakes and prizes.","true","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","62853"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683299","HM Treasury","false","2017-02-10","<p>All HM Treasury employees, contractors and agency staff are subject to National Security vetting and are asked to disclose any criminal convictions which they may have, including spent, in accordance with the Rehabilitation of offenders Act 1974 (Exceptions) Order 1975, and the Rehabilitation of offenders (Northern Ireland) Order 1978 (Exceptions) Order 1979, and spent convictions may be taken into account where National Security is concerned.</p><p> </p><p>It is the Treasury's policy for reasons of confidentiality not to release full details relating to numbers of staff fewer than five, where to do so might lead to the identification of individual cases.</p>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby",,"2017-02-10T13:20:08.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683299/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683299/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683299/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-02-02","Treasury: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many former prisoners have been employed by his Department in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","62969"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683300","Church Commissioners","false","2017-02-06","<p>The three most senior office holders of the Church Commissioners are the First Church Estates Commissioner (Crown Appointment), the Second Church Estates Commissioner (Crown Appointment recommended by Government) and the Third Church Estates Commissioner (Appointed by the Archbishop of Canterbury). This information is published on the website of the Church Commissioners (<a href="https://www.churchofengland.org/about-us/structure/churchcommissioners/commissioners.aspx" target="_blank">https://www.churchofengland.org/about-us/structure/churchcommissioners/commissioners.aspx</a>) and in the annual report. A copy of the annual report is placed in the House of Commons Library as a matter of public record. The holders of the positions are officeholders, not employees. The National Church Institutions do not hold other demographic data.</p>","Meriden","Dame Caroline Spelman",,"2017-02-06T17:19:50.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683300/answer","Biography information for Dame Caroline Spelman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683300/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683300/answer",,,,,"9","Church Commissioners","Church Commissioners","2017-02-02","Church Commissioners: Senior Civil Servants","1","House of Commons","To ask the right hon. Member for Meriden, representing the Church Commissioners, what the (a) ethnicity, (b) gender, (c) disability status, (d) educational background and (e) socio-economic status is of the three most senior officials of the Church Commissioners.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","62877"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683301","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-02-10","<p>The Office for National Statistics annually publish Civil Service employment statistics which includes a breakdown of the Department's officials split by ethnicity, gender, and disability status. This information can be found on the Office for National Statistics website:</p><p><a href="https://www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/datasets/civilservicestatistics" target="_blank">https://www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/datasets/civilservicestatistics</a></p><p> </p><p>Details of educational background and socio-economic status are not publicly available or held centrally.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-02-10T14:53:34.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683301/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683301/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683301/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-02-02","Department for Communities and Local Government: Senior Civil Servants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what the (a) ethnicity, (b) gender, (c) disability status, (d) educational background and (e) socio-economic status is of the three most senior officials of his Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","62878"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683302","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-02-09","<p>This Government takes fraud extremely seriously. The Prevention of Social Housing Fraud Act 2013 increased the deterrent to tenants considering cheating the system, ensuring those who do cheat are detected more easily and punished more severely, and encourages social landlords to take a more proactive approach to tackling tenancy fraud.</p><p>We also provided £19 million funding to help councils tackle tenancy fraud as part of over £35 million government funding to tackle fraud across local government.</p><p>The findings and recommendations of the Government’s Right to Buy fraud working group will be published in due course.</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell","62932","2017-02-09T16:55:07.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683302/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683302/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683302/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-02-02","Right to Buy Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what measures his Department has put in place to tackle fraud and abuse related to the Right to Buy scheme.","false","Biography information for Sir Gerald Howarth","Aldershot","Sir Gerald Howarth","62931"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683303","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-02-09","<p>This Government takes fraud extremely seriously. The Prevention of Social Housing Fraud Act 2013 increased the deterrent to tenants considering cheating the system, ensuring those who do cheat are detected more easily and punished more severely, and encourages social landlords to take a more proactive approach to tackling tenancy fraud.</p><p>We also provided £19 million funding to help councils tackle tenancy fraud as part of over £35 million government funding to tackle fraud across local government.</p><p>The findings and recommendations of the Government’s Right to Buy fraud working group will be published in due course.</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell","62931","2017-02-09T16:55:07.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683303/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683303/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683303/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-02-02","Right to Buy Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what additional safeguards the Government's Right to Buy working group has identified to tackle fraud and abuse of that scheme.","false","Biography information for Sir Gerald Howarth","Aldershot","Sir Gerald Howarth","62932"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683304","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-02-14","<p>I refer the Rt Hon Member to my reply to Question 60366.</p><p>The fiscal impact of the changes on public finances was included as part of the OBR’s policy costings for Autumn Statement 2016, which can be found at:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/571402/Policy_Costings_AS_2016_web_final.pdf</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-02-14T16:08:53.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683304/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683304/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683304/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-02-02","Affordable Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 25 January 2017 to Question 60366, if he will publish his Department's unpublished impact assessment on the changes to the affordable housing programme announced in the Autumn Statement 2016.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","62983"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683305","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-02-09","<p>My department has published all the completed research it has commissioned or produced on the effect of immigration on housing. There are no pieces of unpublished research to place in the Library of the House.</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-02-09T16:53:42.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683305/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683305/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683305/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-02-02","Housing: Immigrants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 30 January 2017 to Question 60963, if he will place in the Library unpublished research on the effect of immigration on housing commissioned or produced by his Department.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","62984"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683306","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-02-09","<p>The Homes and Communities Agency has not identified any customers seeking funding from the Home Building Fund which have identified possible red flags for tax avoidance or evasion.</p><p />","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-02-09T16:55:31.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683306/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683306/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683306/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-02-02","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 2 February 2017 to Question 61611, on housing construction, how many Home and Committees Agency customers who have received funding from the Home Building Fund have had customer identification and verification checks which have identified possible red flags for tax avoidance or evasion.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","62986"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683307","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-02-09","<p>The Home Building Fund lends to UK registered entities and does not gather specific information in relation to their registration for tax purposes. All borrowers are required to confirm that they comply with UK tax legislation and are subject to Know Your Customer and Money Laundering checks as part of the customer due diligence process. Transactions are subject to additional internal controls (referred to as the Offshore Protocol) if the transaction structure involves an offshore party within its hierarchy. Where appropriate additional due diligence and independent tax advice will be taken</p><p> </p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-02-09T16:56:25.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683307/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683307/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683307/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-02-02","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 2 February 2017 to Question 61611, on housing construction, how many organisations that have received funding from the Home Building Fund are registered for tax purposes in (a) one of the Channel Islands and (b) the Isle of Man.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","62987"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683308","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-02-10","<p>This information is not held centrally on either electronic or physical personnel records.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-02-10T14:50:34.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683308/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683308/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683308/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-02-02","Department for Communities and Local Government: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many former prisoners have been employed by his Department in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","62951"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683309","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-10","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-02-10T14:51:32.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683309/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683309/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683309/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-02-02","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many former prisoners have been employed by her Department in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","62952"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683310","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-10","<p>The full time equivalent resource, by grade, currently employed in the Youth Policy Team is as follows:</p><p>1.2 at SCS1</p><p>5 at A grade</p><p>7 at B grade</p><p>This does not include vacancies.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2017-02-10T14:57:39.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683310/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683310/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683310/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-02-02","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many staff of her Department at what grades are employed in the youth policy team.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","62990"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683311","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-08","<p>The UK has demonstrated time and again its abilities in hosting major sporting events and the department is committed to maintaining the nation’s reputation for world-class event delivery. We are aware there are cities interested in hosting the Commonwealth Games and officials have been in discussions to establish the financial and technical feasibility of bringing the Games back to the UK in the future.</p><p> </p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-02-08T10:17:48.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683311/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683311/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683311/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-02-02","Commonwealth Games","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what discussions she has had with Cabinet colleagues on England hosting the Commonwealth Games in 2026; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","62833"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683312","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-10","<p>Due to provisions under the Data Protection Act (1988), we are unable to release information about specific individuals.</p><p> </p><p>Details of DCMS Ministers and Senior Officials are published at https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-culture-media-sport</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-02-10T14:51:21.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683312/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683312/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683312/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-02-02","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Senior Civil Servants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what the (a) ethnicity, (b) gender, (c) disability status, (d) educational background and (e) socio-economic status is of the three most senior officials of her Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","62879"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683314","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-10","<p>The Superfast Rollout programme is technology neutral. This could include Fibre-to-the-cabinet or fibre-to-the-premises solutions along with GFAST, Remote nodes and Fixed wireless or a mix of these</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-02-10T14:51:03.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683314/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683314/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683314/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-02-02","Broadband: Rural Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to her Department's press release of 22 December 2016, whether the £440 million made available for superfast rural broadband only includes costs for traditional and fibre-optic cables; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","62906"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683316","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-02-10","<p>The money returned to projects by efficiency savings and gain-share will be invested using the same criteria set out for the earlier phases of superfast rollout. This means it will focus on areas where there is not commercial competition, and prioritised by value-for-money installations to connect the largest number of premises who do not receive superfast speeds. Urban areas have generally been excluded from Superfast Programmes as commercial competition already exists in these locations.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-02-10T14:50:29.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683316/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683316/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683316/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-02-02","Broadband: Rural Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to her Department's press release of 22 December 2016, whether the £440 million made available for superfast rural broadband will include funding to cover difficult installations or provide access to isolated neighbourhoods.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","62907"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683318","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-07","<p>Creating a rationalised Defence estate, focused around clusters which better support and enhance military capability, will require relocation of functions.</p><p>Where an individual's post is being relocated outside the scope of their personal mobility obligation, they will be managed in accordance with normal Departmental policy and processes. Formal Trades Union consultation will occur well in advance of any closure.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-02-07T16:54:02.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683318/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683318/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683318/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-02","Ministry of Defence: Redundancy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether there will be compulsory redundancies as a result of his Department's site closures.","false","Biography information for Kelvin Hopkins","Luton North","Kelvin Hopkins","62946"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683321","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-07","<p>Details of Ministry of Defence Ministers and Senior Officials are published at https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/ministry-of-defence</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-02-07T16:57:15.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683321/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683321/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683321/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-02","Ministry of Defence: Senior Civil Servants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the (a) ethnicity, (b) gender, (c) disability status, (d) educational background and (e) socio-economic status is of the three most senior officials of his Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","62880"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683323","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-08","<p>The Ministry of Defence is not aware of any occasion since June 2014 when military supplies gifted by the UK Government for use by Kurdistan Regional Government Peshmerga forces in the fight against Daesh have not been allowed by the Government of Iraq.</p><p>The UK Government has trained more than 7,300 Peshmerga fighters in Infantry skills, Counter-IED, engineering and combat first aid and they are playing an invaluable role in defeating Daesh.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-02-08T16:15:07.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683323/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683323/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683323/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-02","Iraq: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the provision of any military supplies agreed by the Government as suitable for the Kurdistan Regional Government has not been allowed by the federal Government of Iraq since June 2014; and if he will make a statement.","true","Biography information for Henry Smith","Crawley","Henry Smith","62865"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683326","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-07","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) is due to dispose of Invicta Park Barracks in 2027. The MOD has held initial discussions with both Kent County Council and Maidstone Borough Council to inform them of our plans, and we will continue to engage with them as our plans to dispose of the site mature.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-02-07T16:49:19.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683326/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683326/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683326/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-02","Invicta Park Barracks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions he has had with (a) Kent County Council and (b) Maidstone Borough Council on the proposed closure of Invicta Park Barracks.","false","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant","62855"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683328","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-07","<p>&quot;A Better Defence Estate&quot; is a military-led review.</p><p>The Department's intent to close Invicta Barracks in 2027 forms part of a strategy to optimise the defence estate to better support our Armed Forces.</p><p>Equality impact assessments are carried out to ensure suitable and appropriate reprovisions are made when sites are actually closed. Therefore, the equality impact assessment will not be undertaken until much later in the disposals process.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-02-07T16:48:47.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683328/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683328/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683328/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-02","Invicta Park Barracks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether an Equality Impact Assessment will be published on the proposal to close Invicta Park Barracks.","false","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant","62856"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683331","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-07","<p>&quot;A Better Defence Estate&quot; is a military-led review.</p><p>The planned disposal date for Invicta Park Barracks is 2027. Following the sale of the site, the value of any receipt will be published as part of the Ministry of Defence's (MOD) annual accounts.</p><p>The MOD cannot publish the cost-benefit analysis on the sale of the Invicta Park Barracks, as to release the information would prejudice the Department's commercial interests. All decisions to dispose of sites were subject to analysis, to ensure they provided the best value for money.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-02-07T16:48:03.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683331/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683331/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683331/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-02","Invicta Park Barracks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will publish his Department's cost-benefit analysis on the sale of the Invicta Park Barracks site prior to that site's selection for closure as part of his Department's Better defence estate strategy.","false","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant","62847"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683333","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-07","<p>The Department's intention to close Invicta Barracks in 2027 forms part of a strategy to optimise the Defence estate to better support our Armed Forces.</p><p> </p><p>The relevant safety assessments will be carried out at Invicta Park Barracks as part of the Department's standard disposals process.</p><p> </p><p>The closure of the site may also contribute to future Government housing targets. Any future uses of the site will be determined by the local authority and the future owner.</p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-02-07T16:51:00.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683333/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683333/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683333/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-02","Invicta Park Barracks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what safety assessment his Department has carried out on the Invicta Park Barracks site to determine whether the land is suitable for house building; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant","62848"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683335","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-07","<p>The information is not held in the format requested.</p><p> </p><p>As of 30 January 2017, Service personnel were deployed in support of UN, EU and NATO operations in the following numbers:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Organisation / Service</p></td><td><p>Royal Navy / Royal Marines</p></td><td><p>Army</p></td><td><p>Royal Air Force</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>UN</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>369</p></td><td><p>3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>EU</p></td><td><p>74</p></td><td><p>12</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>NATO</p></td><td><p>337</p></td><td><p>340</p></td><td><p>88</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-02-07T16:52:46.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683335/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683335/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683335/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-02","Armed Forces: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) Royal Navy, (b) Army and (c) Royal Air Force personnel have been deployed overseas on UN, EU and NATO operations and missions in each of the last five years; and how many such personnel are currently deployed on such operations and missions.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","62859"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683337","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-07","<p>This information is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-02-07T16:53:25.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683337/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683337/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683337/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-02","Armed Forces: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) Royal Navy, (b) Army and (c) Royal Air Force personnel have been deployed overseas on UN, EU and NATO operations and missions on tours exceeding a duration of (i) three, (ii) six and (iii) nine months in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","62860"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683340","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-07","<p>Royal Navy (RN) ships' and submarines' complements are not fixed and vary depending on the nature of the deployment. All RN warships deploy with the personnel required to meet their operational tasking.</p><p>Identifying the personnel assigned aboard deployed warships for the periods requested could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-02-07T16:51:37.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683340/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683340/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683340/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-02","Navy: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Royal Navy personnel have been deployed aboard warships for a  duration exceeding (a) three, (b) six and (c) nine months in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","62861"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683342","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-07","<p>The table below provides in-take to untrained strength for the years requested. Departmental targets are not set down to this level.</p><p> </p><p><strong>Untrained Soldier Intake by Capbadge</strong></p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>2011-12 Actual</p></td><td><p>2012-13 Actual</p></td><td><p>2013-14 Actual</p></td><td><p>2014-15 Actual</p></td><td><p>2015-16 Actual</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Rifles</p></td><td><p>600</p></td><td><p>660</p></td><td><p>410</p></td><td><p>360</p></td><td><p>500</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Brigade of Gurkhas</p></td><td><p>180</p></td><td><p>130</p></td><td><p>130</p></td><td><p>230</p></td><td><p>240</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Parachute Regiment</p></td><td><p>410</p></td><td><p>500</p></td><td><p>300</p></td><td><p>360</p></td><td><p>310</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Royal Irish Regiment</p></td><td><p>110</p></td><td><p>90</p></td><td><p>40</p></td><td><p>80</p></td><td><p>60</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Royal Welsh Regiment</p></td><td><p>270</p></td><td><p>190</p></td><td><p>40</p></td><td><p>70</p></td><td><p>70</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Mercian Regiment</p></td><td><p>430</p></td><td><p>310</p></td><td><p>100</p></td><td><p>180</p></td><td><p>160</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Yorkshire Regiment</p></td><td><p>360</p></td><td><p>300</p></td><td><p>120</p></td><td><p>160</p></td><td><p>170</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Royal Anglian Regiment</p></td><td><p>280</p></td><td><p>170</p></td><td><p>110</p></td><td><p>160</p></td><td><p>160</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Royal Regiment of Fusiliers</p></td><td><p>240</p></td><td><p>140</p></td><td><p>40</p></td><td><p>80</p></td><td><p>80</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Duke of Lancaster Regiment</p></td><td><p>340</p></td><td><p>180</p></td><td><p>120</p></td><td><p>140</p></td><td><p>160</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Princess of Wales Royal Regiment</p></td><td><p>180</p></td><td><p>160</p></td><td><p>100</p></td><td><p>160</p></td><td><p>140</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Royal Regiment of Scotland</p></td><td><p>620</p></td><td><p>450</p></td><td><p>160</p></td><td><p>270</p></td><td><p>210</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Welsh Guards</p></td><td><p>160</p></td><td><p>70</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>60</p></td><td><p>50</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Irish Guards</p></td><td><p>70</p></td><td><p>100</p></td><td><p>40</p></td><td><p>110</p></td><td><p>60</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Scots Guards</p></td><td><p>140</p></td><td><p>110</p></td><td><p>40</p></td><td><p>70</p></td><td><p>40</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Goldstream Guards</p></td><td><p>140</p></td><td><p>160</p></td><td><p>60</p></td><td><p>120</p></td><td><p>80</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Grenadier Guards</p></td><td><p>130</p></td><td><p>120</p></td><td><p>80</p></td><td><p>130</p></td><td><p>100</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>RMAS (Untrained Officers)</p></td><td><p>640</p></td><td><p>560</p></td><td><p>510</p></td><td><p>470</p></td><td><p>520</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><strong><br> </strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong>Notes/Caveats:</strong></p><p> </p><p>The figures are for Regular Army and Gurkhas and therefore exclude the reserve services.</p><p> </p><p>Intake to untrained strength is those who commence Phase 1 training. Targets are set internally and are subject to constant change and review.</p><p> </p><p>Successful applicants are not counted against the intake until they start Phase 1 training.</p><p> </p><p>RMAS figures include only those in the “main” intake, therefore exclude Professionally Qualified Officers (PQO’s).</p><p> </p><p>Intake to untrained Royal Gurkhas Rifles includes all those into the capbadge of the Brigade of Gurkhas – they are then assigned to appropriate trade following basic infantry training.</p><p> </p><p>Figures have been rounded to 10. Figures ending in “5” have been rounded to the nearest multiple of 20 to limit systematic bias.</p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-02-07T17:22:32.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683342/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683342/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683342/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-02","Army: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 1 February 2017 to Question 61395, what the shortfall was for the recruitment of soldiers and officers in (a) The Rifles, (b) Royal Gurkha Rifles, (c) Parachute Regiment, (d) Royal Irish Regiment, (e) Royal Welsh, (f) Mercian Regiment, (g) Yorkshire Regiment, (h) Royal Anglian Regiment, (i) Royal Regiment of Fusiliers, (j) Duke of Lancaster's Regiment, (k) Princess of Wales' Royal Regiment, (l) Royal Regiment of Scotland, (m) Welsh Guards, (n) Irish Guards, (o) Scots Guards, (p) Coldstream Guards, (q) Grenadier Guards and (r) Royal Military Academy Sandhurst in each financial year between 2011-12 and 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","62862"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683345","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-07","<p>Armed forces personnel are currently supporting NATO operations in:</p><p>Afghanistan - Royal Navy, Army, Royal Air Force</p><p>Bosnia - Royal Navy, Army, Royal Air Force</p><p>Estonia - Army</p><p>Kosovo - Army</p><p>Armed forces personnel are currently supporting UN operations in:</p><p>Colombia - Army</p><p>Cyprus - Army</p><p>The Democratic Republic of Congo -Royal Navy, Army</p><p>Italy - Army</p><p>Mali - Army</p><p>Tunisia - Army, Royal Air Force</p><p>Somalia - Royal Navy, Army, Royal Air Force</p><p>South Sudan - Royal Navy, Army, Royal Air Force</p><p>Armed forces personnel are currently supporting EU operations in:</p><p>The Central Mediterranean - Royal Navy, Army, Royal Air Force</p><p>Bahrain - Royal Navy</p><p>Djibouti - Royal Navy</p><p>Mali -Army</p><p>The Seychelles - Royal Navy</p><p>Somalia - Royal Navy</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-02-07T16:55:32.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683345/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683345/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683345/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-02","Armed Forces: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the locations are of UN, EU and NATO operations and missions that personnel from each of the UK armed forces are deployed to.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","62863"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683354","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-09","<p>The information is not held centrally for Service personnel or civil servants and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-02-09T15:36:58.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683354/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683354/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683354/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-02","Ministry of Defence: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many former prisoners have been employed by his Department in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","62953"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683355","Department for Education","false","2017-02-10","<p>The Department does not hold this information.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-02-10T14:02:43.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683355/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683355/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683355/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-02","Department for Education: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many former prisoners have been employed by her Department in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","62954"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683356","Department for Education","false","2017-02-09","<p>The Youth Policy Team moved to Cabinet Office in 2012, therefore information in scope of this response is not held by the Department for Education.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-02-09T16:40:50.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683356/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683356/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683356/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-02","Department for Education: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many staff of her Department at what grade were employed in the youth policy team in July 2014.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","62991"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683357","Department for Education","false","2017-02-10","<p>The Department awarded character grants in the last two years to celebrate the excellent variety of character programmes inside and outside schools across the country. In addition to this, the department also invited bids for the 2016/17 character grants, which we are currently considering.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2017-02-10T14:52:39.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683357/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683357/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683357/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-02","Schools: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, when her Department plans to announce further character award grants.","false","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden","62992"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683358","Department for Education","false","2017-02-07","<p>The statutory guidance provided for in Clause 37 of the Children and Social Work Bill will contain expectations for monitoring and evaluation of pilots. The Government has committed to publically consult on this guidance.</p><p>All pilots will be closely monitored and evaluated. The specific monitoring and evaluation arrangements for any given pilot will be agreed as part of the application, and tailored to the particular details of a pilot. This will include an agreement about conditions under which a pilot would be ended.</p><p>The expert advisory panel will provide published advice on the proposed monitoring and evaluation arrangements of all pilots to ensure they are robust. Information about monitoring and evaluation of pilots will also be contained in the explanatory report, which will accompany regulations laid in Parliament.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","62835 ; 62836 ; 62837","2017-02-07T13:50:59.723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683358/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683358/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683358/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-02","Children: Social Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether she plans for the statutory guidance prescribed in Clause 37 of the Children and Social Work Bill to set out minimum standards for monitoring and evaluation.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","62834"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683359","Department for Education","false","2017-02-07","<p>The statutory guidance provided for in Clause 37 of the Children and Social Work Bill will contain expectations for monitoring and evaluation of pilots. The Government has committed to publically consult on this guidance.</p><p>All pilots will be closely monitored and evaluated. The specific monitoring and evaluation arrangements for any given pilot will be agreed as part of the application, and tailored to the particular details of a pilot. This will include an agreement about conditions under which a pilot would be ended.</p><p>The expert advisory panel will provide published advice on the proposed monitoring and evaluation arrangements of all pilots to ensure they are robust. Information about monitoring and evaluation of pilots will also be contained in the explanatory report, which will accompany regulations laid in Parliament.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","62834 ; 62836 ; 62837","2017-02-07T13:50:59.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683359/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683359/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683359/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-02","Children: Social Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to Chapter 3 of the Children and Social Work Bill and her Department's responsibility to monitor and evaluate pilot periods, whether there is a defined threshold at which trials are to be deemed no longer to be working in the best interests of children.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","62835"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683360","Department for Education","false","2017-02-07","<p>The statutory guidance provided for in Clause 37 of the Children and Social Work Bill will contain expectations for monitoring and evaluation of pilots. The Government has committed to publically consult on this guidance.</p><p>All pilots will be closely monitored and evaluated. The specific monitoring and evaluation arrangements for any given pilot will be agreed as part of the application, and tailored to the particular details of a pilot. This will include an agreement about conditions under which a pilot would be ended.</p><p>The expert advisory panel will provide published advice on the proposed monitoring and evaluation arrangements of all pilots to ensure they are robust. Information about monitoring and evaluation of pilots will also be contained in the explanatory report, which will accompany regulations laid in Parliament.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","62834 ; 62835 ; 62837","2017-02-07T13:50:59.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683360/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683360/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683360/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-02","Children: Social Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to Chapter 3 of the Children and Social Work Bill and her Department's responsibility to monitor and evaluate pilot periods, whether there is a defined trigger that will prompt her to revoke the regulations and immediately stop any trial deemed to be no longer working in the best interests of children.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","62836"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683361","Department for Education","false","2017-02-07","<p>The statutory guidance provided for in Clause 37 of the Children and Social Work Bill will contain expectations for monitoring and evaluation of pilots. The Government has committed to publically consult on this guidance.</p><p>All pilots will be closely monitored and evaluated. The specific monitoring and evaluation arrangements for any given pilot will be agreed as part of the application, and tailored to the particular details of a pilot. This will include an agreement about conditions under which a pilot would be ended.</p><p>The expert advisory panel will provide published advice on the proposed monitoring and evaluation arrangements of all pilots to ensure they are robust. Information about monitoring and evaluation of pilots will also be contained in the explanatory report, which will accompany regulations laid in Parliament.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","62834 ; 62835 ; 62836","2017-02-07T13:50:59.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683361/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683361/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683361/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-02","Children: Social Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to her reference to adverse impacts on children during committee stage of the Children and Social Work Bill on 10 January 2017, what such impacts are in the context of Chapter 3 of the Children and Social Work Bill.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","62837"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683362","Department for Education","false","2017-02-10","<p>All schools are required to teach a balanced and broadly based curriculum that prepares pupils for adult life. The new national curriculum focuses on the essential knowledge so that teachers can design a wider school curriculum that best meets the needs of their pupils.</p><p> </p><p>Many schools already choose to include CPR (cardiopulmonary resuscitation) and defibrillator awareness as part of their PSHE (personal, social, health and economic education) teaching. The non-statutory PSHE programme of study produced by the PSHE Association, teaches young people how to recognise and follow health and safety procedures, ways of reducing risk and minimising harm in risky situations, and how to use emergency and basic first aid.</p><p> </p><p>Many schools also make use of organisations such as the Red Cross and St John Ambulance, to provide information to young people about first aid and dealing with emergencies.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2017-02-10T14:50:17.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683362/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683362/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683362/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-02","First Aid: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will make it her policy for first aid and CPR to be taught in all schools.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","62828"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683363","Department for Education","false","2017-02-09","<p>The Department cannot release information on ethnicity, gender or disability status in relation to specific individuals.</p><p> </p><p>The Department does not hold information about the educational background or socio-economic status of its three most senior officials.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-02-09T10:38:01.09Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683363/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683363/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683363/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-02","Department for Education: Senior Civil Servants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the (a) ethnicity, (b) gender, (c) disability status, (d) educational background and (e) socio-economic status is of the three most senior officials of her Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","62881"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683364","Department for Education","false","2017-02-07","<p>Local authorities have reported their planned expenditure for maintained nursery schools through annual Section 251 returns, showing how they plan to spend their funding from the Dedicated Schools Grant. The hourly rates of funding for delivering the 3 and 4 year-old entitlements in maintained nursey schools are shown below:</p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="2"><p>3 and 4 year-olds</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>2016-17</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Coventry</p></td><td><p>£ 7.29</p></td><td><p>£ 7.34</p></td><td><p>£ 7.52</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>England</p></td><td><p>£ 7.18</p></td><td><p>£ 7.19</p></td><td><p>£ 7.80</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>These rates do not include other sources of funding for maintained nursery schools.</p><p> </p><p>We are providing local authorities with supplementary funding of £55 million a year for their maintained nursery schools. This supplementary funding will allow local authorities to maintain their current levels of funding at least to the end of this Parliament. It will give maintained nursery schools stability during wider changes to the early years funding system whilst also allowing us the time to consult on the future of maintained nursery schools, which we will do in due course.</p><p> </p><p>We have committed to conducting a data assurance exercise in March this year to verify 2016-17 levels of expenditure on maintained nursery schools which will underpin the 2017-18 maintained nursery school local authority allocations of the £55 million.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-02-07T17:34:37.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683364/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683364/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683364/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-02","Pre-school Education: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment she has made of the change in the level of funding for maintained nursery schools in (a) England and (b) Coventry in the last three years; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","62947"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683365","Department for Education","false","2017-02-09","<p>The total number of records, for on roll pupils, included within the 2016 autumn school census was 8,055,271.</p><p>It is our intention to publish information on the new nationality and country of birth information in the form of anonymised research within a statistical report. This will be made available later this year following completion of processing, analysis and assessment of data quality.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-02-09T18:07:57.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683365/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683365/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683365/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-02","Schools: Census","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many children her Department has received information on from the 2016-17 autumn school census; and of those responses how many and what proportions response was (a) refused, (b) not yet obtained and (c) not known to questions on (i) country of birth and (ii) nationality; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","62925"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683366","Department for Education","false","2017-02-09","<p>Institutes of Technology will harness the expertise of employers, both in leadership and design of the curriculum, to help fill local skills gaps. They will specialise in Science, Technology, Engineering and Maths subjects at higher levels and be aligned to the new technical routes set out in the Skills Plan, including engineering and manufacturing. We will set out next steps on the process for establishing Institute of Technology shortly.</p>","Harlow","Robert Halfon",,"2017-02-09T15:29:10.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683366/answer","Biography information for Robert Halfon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683366/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683366/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-02","Engineering: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether the money pledged by the Government in January 2017 for institutes of technology and schools will in part be allocated for aerospace and aviation engineering.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","62905"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683367","Department for Education","false","2017-02-09","<p>This government is committed to widening participation for under-represented groups across all areas of technical education and this applies to Institutes of Technology. These institutions will help to deliver excellence in technical education across the country, providing learners from all backgrounds with a clear route to employment or higher education. We will set out next steps for establishing Institutes of Technology shortly.</p>","Harlow","Robert Halfon",,"2017-02-09T15:25:50.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683367/answer","Biography information for Robert Halfon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683367/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683367/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-02-02","Technology: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how she plans to ensure that girls and women benefit from the money pledged by the Government in January 2017 for institutes of technology and schools.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","62904"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683368","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-03-03","<p>Diversity data is collected from Defra employees through voluntary self-declaration. However, for reasons of anonymity it is not possible to provide a breakdown in the answer as the numbers are too small to report.</p><p>Defra does not collect data on educational background or socio-economic status.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-03-03T11:38:46.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683368/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683368/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683368/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-02-02","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Senior Civil Servants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what the (a) ethnicity, (b) gender, (c) disability status, (d) educational background and (e) socio-economic status is of the three most senior officials of her Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","62882"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683369","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-02-08","<p>The Government is committed to supporting Fairtrade around the world. Over the last six years, the Department for International Development (DfID) has provided £18 million to Fairtrade International to support their work and strengthen the global Fairtrade system. This includes Fairtrade producer and worker organisations that are the drivers of inclusive economic, environmental and social development in their communities around the world. DfID continues to actively engage with Fairtrade on a variety of projects and campaigns, such as the forthcoming Fairtrade Fortnight from 27 February to 12 March.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-02-08T14:06:49.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683369/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683369/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683369/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-02-02","Fairtrade Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if the Government will take steps to encourage more consumers to buy Fairtrade produce.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","62827"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683370","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-02-07","<p>In September, the Secretary of State for Environment announced a ban on trade in worked ivory from the last 70 years, making the UK rules on ivory amongst the toughest in the world. We will be consulting shortly on these plans.</p><p> </p><p>Our consultation will also seek evidence on the benefits and impacts of taking further action, and we welcome evidence from all stakeholders in response to our consultation. I have met with groups on all sides of this debate, from conservation experts to antiques sector representatives, and will continue to do so.</p><p> </p><p>I refer the Honorary Member to the debate on the 6th February</p><p><a href="https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2017-02-06/debates/04A0F6F6-C215-49E0-BF6B-87C55BE1AFE9/DomesticIvoryMarket" target="_blank">https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2017-02-06/debates/04A0F6F6-C215-49E0-BF6B-87C55BE1AFE9/DomesticIvoryMarket</a></p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-02-07T11:38:30.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683370/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683370/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683370/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-02-02","Ivory: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what her Department's policy is on introducing a total ban on the sale of ivory in the UK; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sarah Olney","Richmond Park","Sarah Olney","62854"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683371","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-02-23","<p>Defra is committed to offering job applicants who are former offenders equal and fair opportunities. This commitment is supported through membership and operation of the Business in the Community ‘Ban the Box’ scheme. Following the principles in this scheme, appropriate pre-appointment checks, including a basic criminal record check, are not made until later in the recruitment process.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>However, Defra does not retain details centrally that would allow us to identify former-prisoners so the information requested could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-02-23T15:49:35.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683371/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683371/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683371/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-02-02","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many former prisoners have been employed by her Department in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","62955"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683372","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-08","<p>Having security clearance is a prerequisite for employment with the Foreign and Commonwealth Office. Spent and unspent criminal convictions are inspected as part of security clearance checks.</p><p>We do not keep data on the number of staff or new entrants who have a criminal record and/or spent time in prison.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-02-08T15:04:26.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683372/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683372/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683372/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-02","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many former prisoners have been employed by his Department in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","62957"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683373","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-08","<p>We welcome the political deal signed on 31 December between the Government of the Democratic Republic of Congo and the main political parties. As I said in a statement on 6 January, it is imperative that this deal is implemented as soon as possible so that elections can take place this year. The UK will work to ensure that the elections will be free and fair and collaborate with international partners to support a peaceful transfer of power once the new President has been elected.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-02-08T14:41:51.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683373/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683373/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683373/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-02","Democratic Republic of Congo: Elections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment his Department has made of the effectiveness of the transition of power resulting from planned presidential elections in the Democratic Republic of Congo in 2017.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","62824"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683374","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-08","<p>The information requested is personal data and as such we are unable to provide it because doing so would breach the right to confidentiality of those concerned.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-02-08T15:05:33.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683374/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683374/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683374/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-02","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Senior Civil Servants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what the (a) ethnicity, (b) gender, (c) disability status, (d) educational background and (e) socio-economic status is of the three most senior officials of his Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","62884"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683375","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-10","<p>We are deeply concerned by the verdict in the case against Pastor Hassan Abduelraheen Kodi, Petr Jasek, and Abdulmonem Abdumawlla. We are aware that the defendants have the right to appeal. Officials from our Embassy in Khartoum were present in court for the verdict, and together with our international partners, coordinated attendance at all hearings since their initial arrest. We have regularly raised our concerns over this case directly with the Government of Sudan, most recently on 22 January; and we will continue to do so as part of our ongoing human rights dialogue.</p><p>More widely, freedom of religion or belief in Sudan remains a concern. We continue to urge the Government of Sudan to uphold the commitments of the Interim Constitution of 2005, within which religious freedom is enshrined.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-02-10T12:09:18.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683375/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683375/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683375/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-02","Sudan: Christianity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what reports he has received on the sentence given to Reverend Hassan Abduraheem, Petr Jasek and Abdumonem Abdumawla in Sudan; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mark Durkan","Foyle","Mark Durkan","62866"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683376","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-10","<p>We are deeply concerned by the verdict in the case against Pastor Hassan Abduelraheen Kodi, Petr Jasek, and Abdulmonem Abdumawlla. We are aware that the defendants have the right to appeal. Officials from our Embassy in Khartoum were present in court for the verdict, and together with our international partners, coordinated attendance at all hearings since their initial arrest. We have regularly raised our concerns over this case directly with the Government of Sudan, most recently on 22 January; and we will continue to do so as part of our ongoing human rights dialogue.</p><p>More widely, freedom of religion or belief in Sudan remains a concern. We continue to urge the Government of Sudan to uphold the commitments of the Interim Constitution of 2005, within which religious freedom is enshrined.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-02-10T12:12:14.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683376/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683376/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683376/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-02","Sudan: Religious Freedom","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make an assessment of the effect on freedom of religion or belief in Sudan as a result of the verdict in the recent case related to Reverend Hassan Abduraheem, Petr Jasek and Abdumonem Abdumawla in that country.","false","Biography information for Mark Durkan","Foyle","Mark Durkan","62867"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683377","Department of Health","false","2017-02-09","<p>The General Practice Forward View, published in April 2016, announced that investment in General Practice will increase from £9.6 billion in 2015/16 to over £12 billion by 2020/21, a major financial investment to transform primary care.</p><p> </p><p>Work is underway to increase the primary care workforce and reduce workload, to improve primary care estates and infrastructure, and to redesign care and spread innovation throughout the country.</p><p> </p><p>It is also becoming increasingly normal for general practices to work together at scale in networks or federation of practices, bringing greater opportunities for practices to work collaboratively to strengthen services and their sustainability.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-02-09T11:26:04.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683377/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683377/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683377/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-02","General Practitioners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent assessment he has made of the sustainability of the GP network.","false","Biography information for Oliver Colvile","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Oliver Colvile","62832"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683378","Department of Health","false","2017-02-09","<p>The Department’s Executive team comprises the Permanent Secretary, Chief Medical Officer, Chief Scientific Officer and four Directors General, of which:</p><p> </p><p>- six are White British or Any Other White Background, one is Undeclared;</p><p>- four are female and three are male; and</p><p>- fewer than five have declared disability.</p><p> </p><p>The Department does not hold centrally information on the socio-economic status or education level of its staff members. Further information about the Executive Team is available on the Department’s website.</p><p> </p><p>This is based on the latest available data, which is as at 31 January 2017.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-02-09T11:56:08.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683378/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683378/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683378/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-02","Department of Health: Senior Civil Servants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the (a) ethnicity, (b) gender, (c) disability status, (d) educational background and (e) socio-economic status is of the three most senior officials of his Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","62886"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683379","Department of Health","false","2017-02-09","<p>The proposed timescale for the review of the nutrient profiling model is still currently under review and is now due to be published on gov.uk by the end of February 2017.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-02-09T11:30:49.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683379/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683379/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683379/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-02","Nutrition","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 13 January 2017 to Question 58887, on nutrition, if he will publish on the gov.uk website the proposed timescale for the review of the nutrient profiling model.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","62903"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683380","Department of Health","false","2017-02-07","<p>The net ingredient cost in the community of paracetamol items prescribed in the United Kingdom and dispensed in England in each of the last five years is provided in the following table. The cost reported is at a reimbursement price. This does not take account of the margin that pharmacies earn on the medicines they dispense. This margin is subsequently taken into account as contributing towards the target level of funding for community pharmacies as part of the community pharmacy contractual framework.</p><p> </p><p>Net Ingredient Cost of prescription items of paracetamol dispensed in England in the specified years within British National Formulary 4.7.1 non-opioid analgesics</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Cost of paracetamol prescriptions (£ ‘000s)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>£61,270.1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>£72,039.0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>£81,565.2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>£85,081.2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>£87,619.0</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source: Prescription Cost Analysis</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-02-07T15:42:35.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683380/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683380/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683380/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-02","Paracetamol","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the cost was of prescribing paracetamol on the NHS in each of the last five years; and if he will make statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","62918"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683381","Department of Health","false","2017-02-09","<p>Information on the costs of redundancies and exits in the Department is published in annual resource accounts.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-02-09T10:51:46.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683381/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683381/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683381/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-02","Department of Health: Redundancy Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what redundancy costs were incurred by his Department in each of the last five years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","62928"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683382","Department of Health","false","2017-02-09","<p>In considering policies placed before it, NHS England’s Clinical Priorities Advisory Group followed the published procedure, which was subject to recent public consultation. Policies with the greatest clinical benefit and lowest cost attracted the highest priority recommendation (level 1), while those with lowest clinical benefit and high cost attracted the lowest (level 5). Treatments in level 5 were considered not currently affordable and were not recommended for routine commissioning.</p><p> </p><p>Information on the annual prioritisation process for specialised treatments was announced by NHS England on 4 December 2016. Further information on this announcement can be found here:</p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/2016/12/hiv-prevention-pregramme/" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/2016/12/hiv-prevention-pregramme/</a></p><p> </p><p>NHS England has published whether policies were above or below the threshold for commissioning; there are no plans to publish the individual prioritisation rankings.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-02-09T10:53:57.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683382/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683382/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683382/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-02","Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 26 January 2017 to Question 60527, what priority recommendation level was assigned by the NHS England Clinical Priority Advisory Group to each of the policy proposals (a) recommended for routine commissioning and (b) not recommended for routine commissioning.","false","Biography information for Crispin Blunt","Reigate","Crispin Blunt","62930"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683383","Department of Health","false","2017-02-10","<p>The Department expects to recruit to approximately 340 posts over the next 12 months. All vacancies are advertised on the central Civil Service Jobs website, which does not attract additional costs.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-02-10T13:39:09.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683383/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683383/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683383/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-02","Department of Health: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many civil servants his Department plans to recruit in the next 12 months; and what the cost to the public purse of that recruitment will be.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","62929"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683384","Department of Health","false","2017-02-07","<p>Information about the frequency of emergency ambulance call-outs to prisons is not collected centrally by the Department or NHS England.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-02-07T15:54:58.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683384/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683384/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683384/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-02","Prisoners: Suicide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many times an ambulance has been called to a prison for an inmate who has attempted suicide in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","62838"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683385","Department of Health","false","2017-02-07","<p>Departmental guidance was published in 2011 on best practice to achieve urgent transfers within 14 days. NHS England continues to work with prison healthcare and secure mental health providers to improve processes so that this can be achieved.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England collects data at a national level from Health and Justice Indicators of Performance on prisoner 14 day transfers to hospital under the Mental Health Act 1983.</p><p> </p><p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave her to Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=45018" target="_blank">45018</a> on 8 September 2016 for NHS England’s data for the financial years (FY) 2015/16 and the first quarter of 2016/17.</p><p> </p><p>The latest data for the second quarter 2016/17 is presented in the table:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Period</p></td><td><p>= less than 14 days</p></td><td><p>more than 14 days</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Quarter2 FY 2016-17</p></td><td><p>93</p></td><td><p>182</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-02-07T17:51:44.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683385/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683385/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683385/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-02","Prisoners: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many prisoners have waited for more than 14 days for a transfer to hospital under the Mental Health Act 1983 in each month since April 2015.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","62839"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683386","Department of Health","false","2017-02-10","<p>NHS England publishes quarterly information on the numbers of available and occupied beds open overnight or day only in National Health Service organisations, most recently for quarter 2 of 2016-17.</p><p> </p><p>National time series of these data are available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/bed-availability-and-occupancy/bed-data-overnight/" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/bed-availability-and-occupancy/bed-data-overnight/</a></p><p>and</p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/bed-availability-and-occupancy/bed-data-day-only/" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/bed-availability-and-occupancy/bed-data-day-only/</a></p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-02-10T09:19:40.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683386/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683386/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683386/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-02","Hospital Beds","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of recent trends in the level of availability of NHS beds.","false","Biography information for Ruth Cadbury","Brentford and Isleworth","Ruth Cadbury","62851"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683388","Department of Health","false","2017-02-09","<p>The Department does not hold central records on the number of former prisoners employed within the department.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-02-09T10:56:10.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683388/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683388/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683388/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-02","Department of Health: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many former prisoners have been employed by his Department in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","62959"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683389","Department of Health","false","2017-02-10","<p>It is the Government’s policy that employees should be paid at least the statutory National Living Wage (NLW) introduced in April 2016 and this is the case for all National Health Service staff. NHS trades unions and NHS Employers continue to work in partnership to consider the impact of the NLW on the lowest pay bands within the Agenda for Change pay structure to ensure that staff continue to receive equal pay for work of equal value.</p><p>Based on the current Office for Budget Responsibility forecasts, the NLW is unlikely to affect Agenda for Change staff in 2018/19 or 2019/20.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-02-10T09:15:43.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683389/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683389/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683389/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-02","NHS: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will make it his policy to restructure the most junior Agenda for Change pay bands to (a) pay the living wage and (b) maintain pay differentials.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","62938"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683390","Department of Health","false","2017-02-09","<p>The Government is committed to achieving good health outcomes for children and young people. Local authorities are responsible for commissioning appropriate public health services for 0-5 year olds in their areas, including health visiting.</p><p> </p><p>Provision by local authorities of five universal health visitor reviews for children aged 0-5 was required by Regulations which came into force on 1 October 2015. The Department commissioned Public Health England (PHE) to undertake a review of the Regulations at 12 months.</p><p> </p><p>PHE has completed the review of the mandating of universal health visiting services. The review was informed by looking at existing national and local statistics on health visiting service delivery and health and wellbeing outcomes for young children. In addition, feedback from a number of different stakeholder perspectives, including health visitors, was sought.</p><p> </p><p>PHE’s report is informing next steps decisions about the service and the Department expects to announce these shortly and to publish the report.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","62941","2017-02-09T13:26:51.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683390/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683390/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683390/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-02","Health Visitors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether it is his Department's policy that the mandation of health visiting services will continue after March 2017.","false","Biography information for Helen Hayes","Dulwich and West Norwood","Helen Hayes","62939"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683391","Department of Health","false","2017-02-10","<p>The Government makes its determinations on pay awards informed by recommendations from the independent NHS Pay Review Body (NHS PRB).</p><p> </p><p>The Retail Price Index was discontinued as a national statistic. Consumer Price Inflation (CPI) is a standard measure for understanding changes in earnings in the context of inflation. It is used widely to determine a measure of the real value of earnings and is used by the Bank of England for its 2% inflation target. CPI is an internationally recognised inflation tracker which the independent Pay Review Body also recognise.</p><p> </p><p>We look forward to receiving this year's NHS PRB report shortly.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-02-10T09:17:21.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683391/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683391/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683391/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-02","Nurses: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will make it his policy to implement a pay award for nursing staff in line with the retail price index.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","62940"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683392","Department of Health","false","2017-02-09","<p>The Government is committed to achieving good health outcomes for children and young people. Local authorities are responsible for commissioning appropriate public health services for 0-5 year olds in their areas, including health visiting.</p><p> </p><p>Provision by local authorities of five universal health visitor reviews for children aged 0-5 was required by Regulations which came into force on 1 October 2015. The Department commissioned Public Health England (PHE) to undertake a review of the Regulations at 12 months.</p><p> </p><p>PHE has completed the review of the mandating of universal health visiting services. The review was informed by looking at existing national and local statistics on health visiting service delivery and health and wellbeing outcomes for young children. In addition, feedback from a number of different stakeholder perspectives, including health visitors, was sought.</p><p> </p><p>PHE’s report is informing next steps decisions about the service and the Department expects to announce these shortly and to publish the report.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","62939","2017-02-09T13:26:51.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683392/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683392/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683392/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-02","Health Visitors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will publish Public Health England's review of the mandated health visiting service.","false","Biography information for Helen Hayes","Dulwich and West Norwood","Helen Hayes","62941"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683393","Department of Health","false","2017-02-10","<p>The Births and Deaths Registration Act 1953, as amended, provides for the registration of babies born without signs of life after 24 weeks’ gestation, which is the legal age of viability. Parents of babies who are stillborn after 24 weeks’ gestation receive a medical certificate certifying the stillbirth and, upon registration, can register the baby's name and receive a certificate of registration of stillbirth.</p><p> </p><p>Parliament supported a change to the stillbirth definition from “after 28 weeks” to “after 24 weeks” in 1992, following a clear consensus from the medical profession at that time that the age at which a foetus should be considered able to survive should be changed from 28 to 24 weeks. Medical opinion does not currently support reducing this below 24 weeks of gestation. Therefore, there are no plans to amend the stillbirth definition.</p><p> </p><p>We are aware that some parents find it very distressing that they may not register the birth of a baby born before 24 weeks. However, it is important to recognise there would also be parents distressed at the possibility of having to do so. When a baby is born without signs of life before 24 weeks’ gestation, hospitals may issue a local certificate to commemorate the baby's birth.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-02-10T09:14:20.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683393/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683393/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683393/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-02","Childbirth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether his Department plans to allow registered birth certificates for children born from 20 weeks gestation.","false","Biography information for Maria Caulfield","Lewes","Maria Caulfield","62995"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683394","Department of Health","false","2017-02-07","<p>Details of communications staff numbers and spend on salaries for the Department’s staff are shown in the following table.</p><p> </p><p>On staff numbers, to ensure consistency, the Department has provided information according to the following criteria for public relations and communications staff:</p><p> </p><p>- Press and public relations;</p><p>- Stakeholder relations;</p><p>- Campaigns (including marketing and strategic communications);</p><p>- Digital Communications (not IT/digital service teams); and</p><p>- Internal Communications.</p><p> </p><p>On salary spend for communications staff in the Department, we have provided figures for Financial Years 2013-14, 2014-15 and 2015-16:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Department of Health</p></td><td><p>Number of Communications Staff Full Time Equivalent (FTE)<sup>2</sup></p></td><td><p>Salary costs<sup>1</sup></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>98</p></td><td><p>£5,342,173</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>106.5</p></td><td><p>£5,617,946</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>101</p></td><td><p>£5,645,073</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Notes:</p><p> </p><p><sup>1 </sup>Inclusive of all salary costs for permanent and non-permanent staff.</p><p><sup>2 </sup>Figures are for staff numbers at 31 March for each financial year.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Details of NHS England’s communications staff numbers and spend on salaries is shown in the following table:</p><p><strong> </strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>NHS England</p></td><td><p>Number of Communications Staff (FTE)</p></td><td><p>Estimated on salary costs</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>36</p></td><td><p>£1,916,243</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>43</p></td><td><p>£2,158,703</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>52</p></td><td><p>£2,555,059</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong> </strong></p><p>NHS England has advised that it can only provide estimated salary figures due to the way its accounts are structured. The figures are estimated from averages based on staff bandings.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-02-07T15:38:51.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683394/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683394/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683394/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-02","Department of Health: Information Officers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many (a) of his Department's and (b) NHS England staff are employed in media relations and communications roles; and how much was spent on the salaries of those staff members in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","62974"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683395","Department of Health","false","2017-02-07","<p>NHS England meets quarterly with the Prisons and Probation Ombudsman (PPO). NHS England has not met the PPO to discuss avoidable deaths in custody since 9 January 2017.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-02-07T15:56:20.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683395/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683395/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683395/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-02","Prisoners: Death","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether NHS England has met the Prisons and Probation Ombudsman to discuss avoidable deaths in custody since 9 January 2017.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","62972"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683396","Department of Health","false","2017-02-07","<p>The Department currently has no plans to place Sustainability and Transformation Plans (STPs) on a statutory footing.</p><p> </p><p>STPs represent a coming together of commissioners, providers and local authorities to consider how to best plan care across their entire footprint and deliver the three aims set out in the Five Year Forward View. However, the statutory architecture for health and care remains fully in place, as do the existing accountabilities for Chief Executives and Accountable Officers of providers and clinical commissioning groups.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-02-07T15:51:53.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683396/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683396/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683396/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-02","NHS: Reorganisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether he plans to place the governance arrangements for sustainability and transformation plans on a statutory footing.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","62973"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683397","Department of Health","false","2017-02-07","<p>Data on applicants to nursing, midwifery and allied health profession courses as of the January application deadline was published by UCAS on 2 February 2017 and covers the period between 2013 and 2017. The primary set of statistics covers all applications in the UCAS Undergraduate scheme within this category.</p><p><a href="https://www.ucas.com/corporate/data-and-analysis/ucas-undergraduate-releases/2017-cycle-applicant-figures-%E2%80%93-january-deadline" target="_blank">https://www.ucas.com/corporate/data-and-analysis/ucas-undergraduate-releases/2017-cycle-applicant-figures-%E2%80%93-january-deadline</a></p><p> </p><p>Data prior to this is not held by the Department and may be available from UCAS.</p><p> </p><p>For the January 2017 release, UCAS, for the first time also published a new subset of the sector-level reports for applicants to nursing courses (within subject group ‘B7’). These reports include applicants who have made at least one choice to a ‘B7’ nursing course but does not include a breakdown of Allied Health Professions data.</p><p> </p><p>Students can still apply to study courses up until the middle of September.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-02-07T16:13:01.817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683397/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683397/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683397/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-02","Health Professions: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will publish information his Department holds from UCAS on the number of applications for undergraduate (a) nursing, (b) midwifery and (c) allied health degrees on 15 January 2017 in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","62975"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683398","Department of Health","false","2017-02-10","<p>At this stage of the application cycle, based on the data the Universities and Colleges Admissions Service published on 2 February, Health Education England (HEE) is confident that the National Health Service will be able to fill the number of nursing and midwifery training places in England.</p><p> </p><p>HEE has increased nurse training commissions by nearly 15% over the last three years and is forecasting that up to 40,000 additional nurses could be available to the NHS by 2020.</p><p> </p><p>In addition to the increase in training commissions, HEE has also implemented a number of steps to increase nurse numbers within the NHS. These include:</p><p> </p><p>- proactively promoting the Return to Practice programme, aimed at encouraging previously qualified nurses that have left the NHS, to update their skills and qualifications and return to practice within the NHS;</p><p>- the provision of flexible routes into nursing for pre-existing support staff; and</p><p>- working closely with universities to improve attrition rates from courses which will further increase the number of nursing students who graduate.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","63028","2017-02-10T09:12:49.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683398/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683398/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683398/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-02","Nurses: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what his policy is on increasing the number of nursing graduates.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","62998"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683399","Department of Health","false","2017-02-09","<p>NHS England has regular management discussions with clinical commissioning groups (CCGs), which may encompass the NHS Constitution, the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) guidance and statutory requirements.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has a duty to have regard to the Health and Social Care Act 2012, the NHS Constitution and quality standards prepared by NICE. As part of their general duty to secure a continuous improvement in quality, CCGs also have a duty to have regard to NICE guidance when planning and delivering services.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-02-09T11:25:03.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683399/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683399/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683399/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-02","Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what discussions NHS England has with clinical commissioning groups on commissioning policies and the requirements of the NHS constitution, NICE guidance and the Health and Social Care Act 2012.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","62989"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683400","Home Office","false","2017-02-06","<p>The follow up to the review by Stephen Shaw CBE into the welfare in detention of vulnerable persons will take place in late 2017. The timings and resources for his follow up review are to be agreed with Mr Shaw.</p><p> </p><p>Mr Shaw will be invited to assess the implementation of all his review recommendations.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","62981 ; 62982 ; 62993","2017-02-06T14:05:53.817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683400/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683400/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683400/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-02-02","Welfare in Detention of Vulnerable Persons Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many staff of her Department will support Stephen Shaw in producing the review of his report on immigration detention.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","62997"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683401","Home Office","false","2017-02-07","<p>The immigration rules for study migration currently differentiate by types of institution. We will be shortly consulting on how we could differentiate further to support the sector.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-02-07T15:39:58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683401/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683401/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683401/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-02-02","Higher Education: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of Question 58064, on overseas students, what definition her Department uses to define (a) top universities and (b) best students.","false","Biography information for Christina Rees","Neath","Christina Rees","62976"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683402","Home Office","false","2017-02-07","<p>The Government is committed to bringing down net migration to sustainable levels.</p><p> </p><p>There is no limit to the number of genuine international students who can come to study in the United Kingdom. There are no plans to change this.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-02-07T13:25:13.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683402/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683402/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683402/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-02-02","Immigration Controls","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the Government's policy is on (a) reducing the level of migration to the UK and (b) caps related to international student recruitment.","false","Biography information for Christina Rees","Neath","Christina Rees","62977"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683403","Cabinet Office","false","2017-02-07","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-02-07T16:14:26.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683403/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683403/answer","PQ62978 Harriet Harman V4.0.pdf","UKSA Letter to Member - Resident of EU Countries","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683403/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-02-02","EU Nationals: Southwark","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many people from other EU countries are resident in (a) Camberwell and Peckham constituency and (b) the London Borough of Southwark.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","62978"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683404","Home Office","false","2017-02-06","<p>The follow up to the review by Stephen Shaw CBE into the welfare in detention of vulnerable persons will take place in late 2017. The timings and resources for his follow up review are to be agreed with Mr Shaw.</p><p> </p><p>Mr Shaw will be invited to assess the implementation of all his review recommendations.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","62981 ; 62982 ; 62997","2017-02-06T14:05:54.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683404/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683404/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683404/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-02-02","Welfare in Detention of Vulnerable Persons Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when she expects Stephen Shaw to (a) begin, (b) complete and (c) publish the findings of his review of his report on immigration detention.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","62993"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683405","Home Office","false","2017-02-06","<p>The Home Office does not hold central records on the number of former prisoners employed within the department. Obtaining this information could only be achieved at disproportionate cost.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-02-06T15:59:33.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683405/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683405/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683405/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-02-02","Home Office: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many former prisoners have been employed by her Department in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","62960"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683406","Home Office","false","2017-02-06","<p>The follow up to the review by Stephen Shaw CBE into the welfare in detention of vulnerable persons will take place in late 2017. The timings and resources for his follow up review are to be agreed with Mr Shaw.</p><p> </p><p>Mr Shaw will be invited to assess the implementation of all his review recommendations.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","62982 ; 62993 ; 62997","2017-02-06T14:05:54.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683406/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683406/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683406/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-02-02","Welfare in Detention of Vulnerable Persons Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 19 January 2017 to Question 59369, on immigrant detainees, what the terms of reference are for Stephen Shaw's review.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","62981"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683407","Home Office","false","2017-02-06","<p>The follow up to the review by Stephen Shaw CBE into the welfare in detention of vulnerable persons will take place in late 2017. The timings and resources for his follow up review are to be agreed with Mr Shaw.</p><p> </p><p>Mr Shaw will be invited to assess the implementation of all his review recommendations.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","62981 ; 62993 ; 62997","2017-02-06T14:05:54.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683407/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683407/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683407/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-02-02","Welfare in Detention of Vulnerable Persons Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 19 January 2017 to Question 59369, on immigrant detainees, what the key actions are from Stephen Shaw's previous report.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","62982"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683408","Home Office","false","2017-02-23","<p>Diversity data is personal information, disclosure which could identify an individuals’ personal data would be in breach of our obligations under the Data Protection Act, 1998. Information in respect of ethnicity, gender and disability is confidentially collated and is strictly regulated.</p><p>Diversity data is reported on an anonymised basis so that it is impossible to link the details to individuals, identifying this information for the three most senior officials would make it easy to link the details to individuals therefore we are unable to provide the information requested.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-02-23T12:52:47.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683408/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683408/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683408/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-02-02","Home Office: Senior Civil Servants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the (a) ethnicity, (b) gender, (c) disability status, (d) educational background and (e) socio-economic status is of the three most senior officials of her Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","62887"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683409","Home Office","false","2017-02-06","<p>Where the Home Office decides not to contest an appeal, follow-on actions are completed as quickly as practically possible. The timeframe for will vary for individual cases, especially where a fresh decision is required or the customer needs to provide further information.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-02-06T14:06:56.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683409/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683409/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683409/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-02-02","Immigration: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 1 February 2017 to Question 61835, on immigration: appeals, how long follow-on actions are expected to take if the Home Office decides not to contest a successful appeal.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","62868"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683410","House of Commons Commission","false","2017-02-07","<p>The Commission does not as a matter of principle publish personal data on easily identifiable individuals. Data is collected on ethnicity, gender and disability status of staff on a voluntary basis and with a guarantee of anonymity. Data is not collected on “educational background” or “socio-economic status”. The hon. Member may of course wish to write to individual staff to ask such questions.</p>","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake",,"2017-02-07T11:04:22.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683410/answer","Biography information for Tom Brake","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683410/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683410/answer",,,,,"18","House of Commons Commission","House of Commons Commission","2017-02-02","House of Commons: Senior Civil Servants","1","House of Commons","To ask the right hon. Member for Carshalton and Wallington, representing the House of Commons Commission, what the (a) ethnicity, (b) gender, (c) disability status, (d) educational background and (e) socio-economic status is of the three most senior officials of the House of Commons Commission.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","62888"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683411","Department for International Development","false","2017-02-09","<p>Releasing this data would breach our obligations for holding and processing information under the Data Protection Act 1998.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-02-09T15:15:22.44Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683411/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683411/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683411/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-02-02","Department for International Development: Senior Civil Servants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what the (a) ethnicity, (b) gender, (c) disability status, (d) educational background and (e) socio-economic status is of the three most senior officials of her Department.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","62889"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683412","Department for International Development","false","2017-02-09","<p>DFID provides no direct support for cultural projects in Paraguay.</p><p> </p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2017-02-09T15:13:35.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683412/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683412/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683412/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-02-02","Paraguay: Culture","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much and what proportion of the aid that her Department gives to Paraguay is for cultural projects in that country; and what those projects so funded are.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","62908"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683413","Department for International Development","false","2017-02-08","<p>The UK Government is discussing short-term options to improve port infrastructure in Hodeidah with Gulf countries, the US and the UN. We are also monitoring port capacity across the country.</p><p>We are also calling on all parties to the conflict to protect civilian infrastructure, including Hodeidah port, from further damage; and to restart political talks in order to end the conflict.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-02-08T17:41:17.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683413/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683413/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683413/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-02-02","Yemen: Ports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps her Department is taking to ensure that adequate port infrastructure is in place at Al Hudaydah port and other ports in Yemen for the transmission of international aid to the Yemeni people.","false","Biography information for Nick Smith","Blaenau Gwent","Nick Smith","62668"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683414","Department for International Development","false","2017-02-07","<p>Andargachew Tsege’s consular case was raised during the Secretary of State’s meeting with Prime Minister Hailemariam Desalegn.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2017-02-07T15:26:34.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683414/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683414/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683414/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-02-02","Andargachew Tsege","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether she raised the case of Andrew Tsege during her recent visit to Ethiopia.","false","Biography information for Liz McInnes","Heywood and Middleton","Liz McInnes","62864"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683415","Department for International Development","false","2017-02-09","<p>DFID staff are appointed subject to a security check, which includes a review of any criminal record. DFID cannot confirm if any former prisoners have been employed in the last five years.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-02-09T15:16:16.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683415/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683415/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683415/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-02-02","Department for International Development: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many former prisoners have been employed by her Department in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","62961"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683416","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-09","<p>I refer my Hon Friend to the answer given on 12 December 2016 to the Hon Member for Leeds [Written question – 56955]. Figures for 2016 are not yet available.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-02-09T17:06:37.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683416/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683416/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683416/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-02","Prisons: Crimes of Violence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many prisoners were given extra days in prison for assaulting a prison officer in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","62942"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683417","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-09","<p>Data on the number of prisoners released on temporary license (ROTL), of which resettlement overnight release is one type, is published quarterly, and data for each year going back to 2002 is published on gov.uk.</p><p> </p><p>We reviewed the approach to ROTL in 2013 to ensure risks are being managed effectively and there is now a greater focus on: linking the ROTL activity to the individual’s sentence plan; countering any presumption to temporary release; and, an improved risk assessment and management approach, particularly with the most serious offenders. This has, however, had an unintended consequence – restrictions to improve risk management of the most serious offenders, have resulted in lower risk offenders not being able to benefit from ROTL.</p><p> </p><p>We will maintain the improvements made while allowing governors greater discretion in how they tailor their ROTL regime to the circumstances of each offender. We know that three of the most powerful factors helping to keep ex-offenders from re-offending are a good job, strong family ties and a stable place to live - ROTL makes all of them easier to achieve. Public protection is our top priority and we have no intention of changing the full risk-assessment offenders on ROTL must undergo and any non-compliance will be dealt with robustly.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-02-09T17:17:33.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683417/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683417/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683417/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-02","Prisoners' Release","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what assessment she has made of trends in the number of prisoners temporarily released on resettlement overnight release licences in each of the last five years; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","62943"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683418","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-09","<p>As we announced in the House of Lords last month, we will set out our strategy for victims within 12 months, and will take the appropriate action to give effect to the strategy, including bringing forward any appropriate primary legislation.</p><p>We have made some positive steps to improve the experience of victims of crime, to reduce unnecessary stress and lessen the emotional turmoil of attending court. For example, this year we began rolling out pre-trial cross-examination for vulnerable victims and witnesses in the Crown Court. However more can be done to further strengthen the rights of victims.</p><p>We are considering how compliance with the Code of Practice for Victims of Crime (Victims’ Code) might be improved and monitored. We are also exploring how those responsible for delivery of rights and entitlements might be better held accountable for any failings.</p><p>On 6 February I met with the Victims’ Panel which has been re-established so that we can learn from the experiences of victims of crime. I also have regular meetings with the Victims’ Commissioner, Baroness Newlove, about her work in keeping under review the operation of the Victims’ Code. Plans to engage with and obtain views of victims and victims’ groups are being developed.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee","62934","2017-02-09T15:59:35.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683418/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683418/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683418/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-02","Crime: Victims","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether victims of crime will be invited to submit details of their experiences as part of the review of the victims code.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","62944"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683419","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-07","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-02-07T15:48:23.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683419/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683419/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683419/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-02","Ministry of Justice: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many former prisoners have been employed by her Department in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","62963"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683420","Department of Health","false","2017-02-07","<p>Information is not held in the format requested, and such information as is available could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-02-07T15:52:59.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683420/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683420/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683420/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-02","Healthy Start Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 31 January 2017 to Question 61891, on the Healthy Start Scheme, how many people have received support through that scheme since 2010.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","62842"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683421","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-13","<p>The table below shows how much the Prisons and Probation Ombudsman has spent on investigations into self-inflicted deaths from 2010/11 to 2015/16. This covers the salary costs of managers, investigators, and administrative staff including interview transcribers, family liaison officers and fees for call-off investigators. It also includes travel and incidental expenses.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Total</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>£1,444,382</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>£1,374,744</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>£1,409,137</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>£1,372,905</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>£1,371,547</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>£1,278,552</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government believes that prisons should be places of safety and reform. It is concerned by the number of self-inflicted deaths and is committed to reducing it. The recent White Paper set out specific steps that we are taking to improve safety. They include investing over £100m to recruit an additional 2,500 staff across the estate by the end of 2018.</p><p> </p><p>The National Offender Management Service is undertaking a suicide and self-harm reduction project, led by an experienced prison governor, which is driving work in this area. The work includes implementing the recommendations of a review of the Assessment, Care in Custody and Teamwork (ACCT) process, the multi-disciplinary case management process that is the main tool for managing prisoners at risk of suicide and self-harm. This includes the roll out of new training that will help improve staff understanding of suicide and self-harm, including a module designed to raise awareness of mental health issues and to equip staff to respond appropriately to prisoners experiencing mental health problems.</p><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-02-13T14:39:09.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683421/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683421/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683421/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-02","Suicide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much the Prisons and Probation Ombudsman has spent on investigations into self-inflicted deaths in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","62840"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683422","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-09","<p>Community Rehabilitation Companies (CRCs) are not contractually required to report on staffing numbers. All CRCs are contractually required to maintain a professional and appropriately skilled workforce to deliver the services set out in their contracts. We robustly contract manage each CRC to make sure they fulfil their contractual commitment to maintain service delivery, reduce reoffending, protect the public and deliver value for money for taxpayers.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-02-09T17:23:00.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683422/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683422/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683422/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-02","Probation: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many probation staff employed by the Community Rehabilitation Company in Wales have (a) been offered and (b) accepted the enhanced voluntary redundancy scheme since the start of financial year 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","62849"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683423","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-09","<p>In the competition to award contracts to manage the 21 Community Rehabilitation Companies (CRCs), all bidders were rigorously assessed against robust quality, legal, commercial and financial criteria. The bid accepted by the Ministry of Justice (MoJ) from Working Links for the contracts to run the Wales, Devon Dorset and Cornwall and Bristol, Gloucester, Somerset and Wiltshire CRCs included the restructuring of the way services were delivered and the implementation of a new operating model. A thorough evaluation process was undertaken to assess the operational viability of this bid in the wider context of rehabilitation, public protection and reducing reoffending, and plans to realise efficiencies across the business.</p><p> </p><p>Nothing in the department’s contracts with the CRCs owned by Working Links has changed as a result of the sale and due diligence investigations were carried out prior to the sale to make sure services will continue to be satisfactorily provided. The Working Links CRCs are continuing to provide services in accordance with their contracts and are being robustly managed by our contract management teams to make sure they fulfil their contractual obligations in relation to service delivery, reducing reoffending, protecting the public and providing value for money to the taxpayer.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","62822 ; 62823","2017-02-09T17:06:44.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683423/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683423/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683423/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-02","Aurelius","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what competitive tendering process was followed prior to Aurelius taking control of the Community Rehabilitation Company from Working Links in Wales and the West Country.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","62821"
