"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682968","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-06","<p>Out-of-date Operational Ration Packs (ORPs) are withdrawn from use and disposed of in line with current food safety legislation.</p><p> </p><p>Based on information recorded on Ministry of Defence Inventory Management systems, the number of ORPs that have been disposed of is given below. The weight of these disposals is not recorded.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Financial Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number of ORPs</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>63,090</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>110</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>5,004</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>10,798</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April 2016/December 2016</p></td><td><p>12,275</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Notes:</p><p>(1) Information prior to 1 April 2012 is not held.</p><p>(2) Both individual 24-hour ORPs and 10-man ORPs are included in the above figures.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-02-06T16:30:49.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682968/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682968/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682968/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-01","Armed Forces: Food","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) operational ration packs and (b) tonnes of food that represents have been withdrawn from use and disposed of in each of the last five years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","62725"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682969","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-02-07","<p>During a recent call with Secretary of State for Defence, US Defense Secretary Mattis emphasised the United States' continued firm commitment to NATO.</p><p>This was reiterated during the Prime Minister's visit to the US, where President Trump stated that he is '100 per cent behind' NATO.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-02-07T17:05:24.46Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682969/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682969/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/682969/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-02-01","NATO","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment his Department has made of the potential diminishment of US commitment to NATO after President Trump's reorganisation of the US National Security Council.","false","Biography information for Danny Kinahan","South Antrim","Danny Kinahan","62692"
