"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683036","Department of Health","false","2017-02-09","<p>Most new medicines and significant licence extensions for existing medicines are referred to the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) for consideration through its technology appraisal programme. NICE makes recommendations to the National Health Service on whether treatments represent a clinically and cost effective use of NHS resources. NHS commissioners are legally required to fund drugs and other treatments recommended in NICE technology appraisal guidance, normally within three months of publication of final guidance.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-02-09T11:29:28.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683036/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683036/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683036/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-01","NHS: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to ensure that new medicines introduced on the NHS are (a) medically and (b) cost effective.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","62765"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683037","Department of Health","false","2017-02-08","<p>NHS England has advised that the in vitro fertilisation (IVF) benchmark price will be developed during 2017/18 with support from the IVF Expert Advisory Group and all key stakeholders, working towards publishing the IVF benchmark price ready for the financial year 2018/19. It is also planning to develop and test an IVF outcome based payment approach with a number of clinical commissioning groups and service providers in 2018/19.</p><p> </p><p>The issue of an IVF benchmark price was first raised at a meeting with my hon. Friend the former Parliamentary Under Secretary of State for Public Health (Jane Ellison) on 14 December 2015, attended by NHS England officials and stakeholders. There was a subsequent follow up meeting between the Department and NHS England on 10 May 2016. NHS England met with professionals groups and stakeholders on 24 June 2016 and established the IVF Expert Advisory Group, whose membership includes NHS England, the Department, National Health Service commissioners, the Human Fertilisation and Embryology Authority, professional groups and patient stakeholders. The Expert Advisory Group met for the first time on 11 November 2016 and is scheduled to meet again on 3 March 2017. A wider stakeholder workshop also took place on 9 December 2016.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","62749","2017-02-08T16:24:52.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683037/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683037/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683037/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-01","In Vitro Fertilisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many meetings his Department has had with (a) NHS England, (b) professional bodies and (c) stakeholder bodies to discuss the creation of a benchmark price for IVF.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","62750"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683038","Department of Health","false","2017-02-09","<p>Information concerning the number of people living with a diagnosis of epilepsy in each of the last five years is not collected. However, the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence estimates that epilepsy affects between 362,000 and 415,000 people in England. Total spend on treating individual neurological conditions, such as epilepsy, is not available.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat","62764","2017-02-09T11:19:05.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683038/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683038/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683038/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-01","Epilepsy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many people have been living with a diagnosis of epilepsy in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","62762"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683039","Cabinet Office","false","2017-02-09","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-02-09T15:09:12.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683039/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683039/answer","Response to PQ62763.pdf","UKSA response to PQ62763","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683039/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-02-01","Epilepsy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many people have died as a result of symptoms relating to epilepsy in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","62763"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683040","Department of Health","false","2017-02-09","<p>Information concerning the number of people living with a diagnosis of epilepsy in each of the last five years is not collected. However, the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence estimates that epilepsy affects between 362,000 and 415,000 people in England. Total spend on treating individual neurological conditions, such as epilepsy, is not available.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat","62762","2017-02-09T11:19:05.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683040/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683040/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683040/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-01","Epilepsy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the cost to the NHS has been of treating people with a diagnosis of epilepsy in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","62764"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683041","Department of Health","false","2017-02-08","<p>NHS England has advised that the in vitro fertilisation (IVF) benchmark price will be developed during 2017/18 with support from the IVF Expert Advisory Group and all key stakeholders, working towards publishing the IVF benchmark price ready for the financial year 2018/19. It is also planning to develop and test an IVF outcome based payment approach with a number of clinical commissioning groups and service providers in 2018/19.</p><p> </p><p>The issue of an IVF benchmark price was first raised at a meeting with my hon. Friend the former Parliamentary Under Secretary of State for Public Health (Jane Ellison) on 14 December 2015, attended by NHS England officials and stakeholders. There was a subsequent follow up meeting between the Department and NHS England on 10 May 2016. NHS England met with professionals groups and stakeholders on 24 June 2016 and established the IVF Expert Advisory Group, whose membership includes NHS England, the Department, National Health Service commissioners, the Human Fertilisation and Embryology Authority, professional groups and patient stakeholders. The Expert Advisory Group met for the first time on 11 November 2016 and is scheduled to meet again on 3 March 2017. A wider stakeholder workshop also took place on 9 December 2016.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","62750","2017-02-08T16:24:52.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683041/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683041/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/683041/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-01","In Vitro Fertilisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the timescale is for deciding and publishing the benchmark price for IVF.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson",